# Test Reporting System Guide

## Overview

The test reporting system generates standardized reports for test execution and checklist completion. Reports are stored in `.codespaces/testing/.test/results/`.

## Report Types

1. Feature Test Reports
   - Generated after each test suite execution
   - Named: `feature-test-report-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.md`
   - Contains detailed test results

2. Test Tracking Data
   - JSON format
   - Stored in `.codespaces/testing/.test/tracking/`
   - Named: `test-tracking-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.json`

## Report Contents

### Feature Test Reports

```markdown
# Feature Test Report
Generated: [timestamp]

## Summary
- Total Tests
- Completed Tests
- Passed Tests
- Failed Tests
- Skipped Tests
- Duration
- Status

## Checklist Status
- Total Items
- Completed Items
- Pending Items
- Failed Items

## Test Suites
[Detailed test suite results]
```

### Test Tracking Data

```json
{
    "StartTime": "timestamp",
    "EndTime": "timestamp",
    "TotalTests": number,
    "CompletedTests": number,
    "PassedTests": number,
    "FailedTests": number,
    "SkippedTests": number,
    "TestSuites": [...],
    "Status": "string"
}
```

## Report Generation

Reports are automatically generated:
1. After each test suite execution
2. When tests complete
3. When errors occur
4. At the end of the test run

## Report Integration

Reports are integrated with:
- Test execution tracking
- Checklist system
- Error logging
- Test results storage

